---------------------------------
Crunchbang Screenshot Info Script
---------------------------------
Prints your current Openbox, GTK, Icon and Font themes then takes a screenshotafter a 5 second delay. The screenshot is then saved to your home directory. The current config is setup for Crunchbang Openbox users,however the distribution, window manager and desktop environment can be changed by editing info.pl. 

This script is provided with absolutely no warranty, by running this script you
acknowledge that it may blow up your computer, shave your dog, or wake your 
neighbors . If you modify this script I'd love to see what youv'e done. 
Feel free to email me at jinnstar@jinnfire.info.

---------------------------------
Requirements:
---------------------------------
Perl - most *nix systems already have this
Scrot - the script uses this app to take the actual screenshots.

---------------------------------
Installation:
---------------------------------
1: ## Extract the CBInfo.tar.gz with:
   tar -xvzf CBInfo.tar.gz
    
2:  ## Create a folder called bin/ in your home directory
    mkdir ~/bin

3:  ## Copy the script to your new directory
    cp CBInfo/info.pl ~/bin

4:  ## Switch to the new directory
    cd ~/bin

5:  ## Make the script executable  
    chmod +x info.pl

6:  ## Run the script
    ./info.pl
